# Fix: blank Syy / Syu PSD plots in system-ID script

## Context
When running `run_system_id_and_gain_design.m`, the `Syy` (output auto-PSD) and
`Syu` (cross-PSD) plots come up blank, while `Suu` (input auto-PSD) renders fine.

### Root cause (confirmed)
- **`run_system_id_and_gain_design.m:46`** — `q_rps = interp1(measured_time, measured_rate, chirp_time_s)`.
  The final command timestamp (763.856 s) falls just past the last angular-velocity
  measurement, so `interp1` (no extrapolation) returns **1 NaN** at the end of `q_rps`.
  (Verified via MATLAB: `cmd above meas end: 1`, `NaNs in q_rps: 1 of 35581`.)
- **`Utilities/nonlinear_detrend.m:7`** — `theta_d = (X_d' * X_d) \ (X_d' * z)` sums over
  the whole signal, so that single NaN makes the cubic-fit coefficients NaN and the
  **entire** detrended `q_rps` NaN.
- **`estimate_freq_response.m` → `compute_psd`** — `Y = fft(data_y)` is then all-NaN, so
  `Syy = Y·conj(Y)` and `Syu = Y·conj(U)` are NaN (blank in `semilogy`), while
  `Suu = U·conj(U)` is unaffected because `dele_total` has no NaN.

The same NaN also blanks the Bode/coherence results downstream (`coherence` NaN →
`idx_keep` all false), so this fix repairs more than just the PSD plots.

## Change
**File:** `/home/choudhury/analysis/flight_tests/oddjob/oddjob_chirps_05-19-26/flightLogs/sysID_test/run_system_id_and_gain_design.m`

After the interpolation block (currently lines 44-46), drop any samples where the
interpolation produced NaN, so no NaN ever reaches the detrend / FFT:

```matlab
chirp_time_s = command_time;
dele_total   = command_defl;
q_rps        = interp1(measured_time, measured_rate, chirp_time_s);

% Drop command samples that fall outside the measurement time range
% (interp1 returns NaN there; a single NaN poisons the cubic detrend and FFT).
valid        = ~isnan(q_rps);
chirp_time_s = chirp_time_s(valid);
dele_total   = dele_total(valid);
q_rps        = q_rps(valid);
```

This is surgical and local — it does not touch the shared `sysID_tool` library.
Trimming the trailing out-of-range sample also keeps the later uniform-grid resample
(lines 73-75) within range, so no new NaN is introduced there.

## Not changing (noted, out of scope)
- Title mislabeling in `sysID_tool/estimate_freq_response.m:94,99` — subplot titled
  "Syy" plots `Suu` and vice-versa. Pre-existing bug in the shared repo, unrelated to
  the blank-plot symptom. Mention to user; fix only if they ask.

## Verification
1. Re-run `run_system_id_and_gain_design.m` in MATLAB.
2. Confirm `sum(isnan(q_rps)) == 0` after the trim.
3. The "PSD Calc -- Freq Domain" figure now shows curves in all three columns
